WEBVTT

00:01.278 --> 00:04.058
[SPEAKING GREEK] _

00:04.970 --> 00:08.390
[SPEAKING GREEK] _

00:09.280 --> 00:12.460
You know Troy started a war over an apple?

00:12.560 --> 00:14.294
Dad, are you gonna talk to me?

00:14.560 --> 00:15.820
- Take it.
- [SPEAKS GREEK]

00:15.920 --> 00:17.280
- [CHUCKLES]
- [TRADITIONAL MUSIC PLAYING]

00:17.360 --> 00:19.597
What are you going back
to that den of wolves for?

00:19.794 --> 00:21.614
[CHUCKLES] I was born in the States, Dad.

00:21.714 --> 00:23.806
- It's a good job.
- You got a good job here with me.

00:23.831 --> 00:25.079
Your place is with me.

00:25.154 --> 00:27.314
We're pushing the boundaries
of science, of what is possible.

00:27.394 --> 00:29.354
You wanna go back there and
do some staid, non-credited,

00:29.434 --> 00:32.374
- boring government job, Christos?
- Dad, I-I wanna go home.

00:33.075 --> 00:34.972
Christos, your home is here.

00:34.997 --> 00:37.417
You're going to graduate
and you're gonna stay here,

00:37.613 --> 00:41.044
with me, where you belong,
in my lab, in <i>our</i> lab.

00:41.994 --> 00:43.747
Don't turn your back on me, son.

00:44.487 --> 00:45.916
We're gonna do great things, you and me.

00:45.941 --> 00:47.001
[CHUCKLES]

00:48.114 --> 00:50.494
♪

00:51.874 --> 00:54.346
VELLEK: Thing of beauty. <i>Perfezione.</i>

00:54.835 --> 00:56.476
FLETCHER: The Rust is completely gone.

00:56.790 --> 00:58.650
That is truly something, Dr. Vellek.

00:58.750 --> 01:00.236
"Something," Fletcher?

01:00.750 --> 01:03.242
In 24 hours, I wiped out the Red Rust,

01:03.550 --> 01:05.489
and in its place, I
created, <i>sui generis,</i>

01:05.590 --> 01:07.170
a completely new species of plant.

01:07.270 --> 01:08.170
A healthy plant.

01:08.270 --> 01:09.770
It's not "something," Fletcher.

01:09.870 --> 01:13.130
This is the transformation
of history. It's Galileo.

01:13.230 --> 01:16.010
Einstein, even. It's beautiful, Father.

01:16.110 --> 01:17.250
Thank you, Lucia.

01:17.846 --> 01:21.387
Very soon, your country
will eat again as kings.

01:21.997 --> 01:23.133
I'm relieved.

01:23.309 --> 01:25.409
'Cause of what I've
done here, me and my son.

01:26.247 --> 01:28.159
It was you, Dad. It was always you.

01:28.259 --> 01:30.399
Father, we need to talk
about the American ship.

01:30.499 --> 01:32.519
- What about it?
- They'll be coming after us.

01:32.619 --> 01:33.909
So what? It's one ship.

01:34.585 --> 01:36.102
Stavros commands an entire fleet.

01:36.459 --> 01:37.579
Surely you can take care of one

01:37.659 --> 01:39.199
United States Navy ship, Admiral?

01:39.299 --> 01:40.359
Of course, <i>il dottore.</i>

01:40.459 --> 01:42.168
The problem's <i>è finite. Finito.</i>

01:42.387 --> 01:44.587
I'm not even gonna get angry
at my middle son, Giorgio,

01:44.667 --> 01:46.287
who can't seem to take one step

01:46.387 --> 01:48.247
without putting his foot in a pile of dung.

01:48.853 --> 01:49.753
Look...

01:49.778 --> 01:50.754
[GLASSES CLATTER]

01:50.779 --> 01:52.661
This is <i>our</i> beginning...

01:54.976 --> 01:57.518
and the end of anyone
who stands in our way.

01:59.527 --> 02:00.647
<i>Capisce?</i>

02:02.333 --> 02:03.258
Good.

02:09.309 --> 02:12.918
[DRAWERS OPEN, CLOSE]

02:17.799 --> 02:19.407
Giorgio, where's Demetrius?

02:20.159 --> 02:21.669
Otherwise occupied.

02:22.639 --> 02:25.119
And since when is Stavros an admiral?

02:26.479 --> 02:28.299
A reward from my father.

02:28.936 --> 02:31.717
Apparently, he earned it.

02:33.467 --> 02:35.565
Your father's quite
harsh with you, isn't he?

02:35.771 --> 02:37.371
I risked my life for him.

02:37.771 --> 02:40.129
That American bitch
nearly blew my head off.

02:41.099 --> 02:43.317
The one from the ship
with the long black hair

02:43.466 --> 02:44.966
and the serious attitude?

02:45.066 --> 02:46.646
You know... Sasha.

02:46.747 --> 02:49.247
Yeah, but the old man
doesn't give a rat's ass.

02:49.347 --> 02:52.508
All he cares about are is
hippie mind control drugs.

02:53.267 --> 02:54.888
Mind control drugs?

02:56.034 --> 02:57.387
What are you talking about?

03:00.672 --> 03:01.886
Leave me alone, Fletcher.

03:02.868 --> 03:04.467
I am not in the mood.

03:08.709 --> 03:10.607
[ASCENDING FOOTSTEPS]

03:11.199 --> 03:19.159
♪

03:20.307 --> 03:28.228
♪

03:29.818 --> 03:35.831
♪

03:36.183 --> 03:38.731
Synced and corrected by louvette
www.addic7ed.com

03:44.020 --> 03:45.780
Vellek wants to feed the world on his terms

03:45.868 --> 03:48.178
and neutralize anyone
who tries to oppose him.

03:48.375 --> 03:50.275
Same as every tyrant in history.

03:50.375 --> 03:52.571
He's just come up with a novel plan.

03:53.095 --> 03:54.695
That's why the world still needs people

03:54.775 --> 03:56.470
with "level nine" aggression.

03:57.255 --> 03:58.686
You think that's a good thing?

04:00.002 --> 04:01.578
If only to fight fire with fire.

04:01.617 --> 04:02.695
Think about it.

04:02.695 --> 04:03.975
Without your aggression,
would you have been able

04:04.055 --> 04:05.495
to do what it took to bring home the cure?

04:05.920 --> 04:07.940
Your dark side saved humanity.

04:08.040 --> 04:09.300
At the cost of my own.

04:09.812 --> 04:11.712
Tom, if you weren't who you are,

04:11.835 --> 04:13.265
none of us would be here right now.

04:14.092 --> 04:15.872
MEYLAN: And that's if
we can find him at all.

04:16.377 --> 04:17.392
SLATTERY: Captain.

04:17.601 --> 04:20.190
Based on Vellek's communication
with Giorgio's mansion,

04:20.220 --> 04:22.640
and with the top speed of
a Hydra class destroyer,

04:22.666 --> 04:25.614
this is now our area of uncertainty.

04:26.028 --> 04:27.768
That's at least 250 nautical miles.

04:28.489 --> 04:30.688
Even with the helo and the RHIB,
we can't cover that much water.

04:30.713 --> 04:32.797
Giorgio make contact with
anyone besides the lab?

04:34.145 --> 04:35.373
- [BEEP]
- Yes, sir.

04:36.019 --> 04:39.079
He made at least a dozen
calls to the same location

04:39.171 --> 04:41.311
over the past few weeks, on land.

04:41.419 --> 04:42.339
Where?

04:43.219 --> 04:44.792
The island of Kleos.

04:45.639 --> 04:46.915
Mean anything to you?

04:47.139 --> 04:48.706
Giorgio never mentioned it.

04:48.871 --> 04:50.651
Kleos. It was an ancient Lazaretto,

04:50.751 --> 04:54.069
a quarantine/prison during the Black Death.

04:54.483 --> 04:56.670
The Italians reopened it
at the height of the Red Flu

04:56.733 --> 04:58.116
to try to stop the spreading.

04:58.413 --> 04:59.936
Obviously, no one survived.

05:00.020 --> 05:01.760
Land of the dead. Wonderful.

05:02.363 --> 05:03.852
[INHALES DEEPLY] What's
Vellek using it for?

05:04.363 --> 05:06.299
Traffic data suggests a relay station,

05:06.628 --> 05:08.868
probably to mask communications
to and from his ship.

05:08.948 --> 05:10.688
With Giorgio's mansion compromised,

05:10.788 --> 05:12.954
it may be the only way for
Vellek to get secure comms.

05:13.594 --> 05:15.312
We can tap into that satellite signal,

05:15.337 --> 05:17.047
use the communications
log to find that ship.

05:17.063 --> 05:18.503
You'd have to do it from the source, sir.

05:18.528 --> 05:19.748
The island itself.

05:19.773 --> 05:21.650
Kleos is about a hundred
miles from our PIM.

05:22.000 --> 05:23.322
We could be there in three hours.

05:24.050 --> 05:25.986
That's away from our area of uncertainty.

05:26.057 --> 05:27.777
If it doesn't work, we'll
lose Vellek for good.

05:27.857 --> 05:30.557
But if it does, we'll have a constant feed

05:30.657 --> 05:32.250
into his comms in real time.

05:32.537 --> 05:34.524
We'll know exactly where he is.

05:35.876 --> 05:37.487
Set course for Kleos.

05:37.796 --> 05:39.244
Cooper, assemble a team.

05:40.876 --> 05:43.796
♪

05:46.116 --> 05:47.664
This room's off-limits.

05:48.437 --> 05:49.805
On whose orders?

05:51.660 --> 05:53.085
We are radio silent.

05:53.848 --> 05:55.108
No calls in or out.

05:55.208 --> 05:58.028
I need to speak with
England, make arrangements

05:58.129 --> 05:59.929
for them to take possession
of the cured seeds.

06:00.009 --> 06:02.749
No need. Those arrangements
have already been made.

06:03.910 --> 06:05.088
Well, if it's all the same with you,

06:05.113 --> 06:06.729
I'd like to hear that for myself.

06:10.035 --> 06:12.504
Fine. I'll take it up with Demetrius.

06:13.596 --> 06:15.029
It will do you no good.

06:18.393 --> 06:19.559
I'm in charge now.

06:19.795 --> 06:23.695
♪

06:23.795 --> 06:27.235
[WEAPONS CLICKING,
INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS]

06:28.195 --> 06:30.135
♪

06:30.945 --> 06:32.015
[GUN COCKS]

06:32.475 --> 06:40.095
♪

06:40.195 --> 06:44.775
♪

06:46.289 --> 06:49.189
[KEYBOARD CLACKING, COMPUTER CHIRPING]

06:49.777 --> 06:51.154
Captain's in combat.

06:51.657 --> 06:54.015
♪

06:54.070 --> 06:56.290
- RHIB is 15 mikes out, sir.
- Very well.

06:57.146 --> 06:59.936
We do this right, Vellek will
never even know we were there.

07:00.546 --> 07:01.678
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

07:01.703 --> 07:03.860
Demetrius, are you in
there? It's James Fletcher.

07:06.226 --> 07:07.526
[KNOCKS ON DOOR]

07:07.626 --> 07:08.891
Demetrius, can I come in?

07:08.917 --> 07:10.827
I cannot let anyone inside.

07:13.186 --> 07:15.534
[DOOR RATTLES]

07:16.245 --> 07:17.846
[LOWERED VOICE] Demetrius, let me in.

07:17.946 --> 07:24.614
♪

07:29.746 --> 07:30.946
[DOOR CLOSES]

07:35.702 --> 07:36.885
What's happened to you?

07:38.732 --> 07:40.158
They did something to me.

07:41.012 --> 07:43.478
Dr. Vellek... he drugged me.

07:44.132 --> 07:45.373
Because you challenged him?

07:45.612 --> 07:50.672
♪

07:51.524 --> 07:52.803
And now you can't?

07:53.284 --> 07:56.384
♪

07:56.484 --> 07:57.725
Mind control.

07:58.084 --> 08:00.504
♪

08:00.604 --> 08:01.785
Stand up.

08:02.284 --> 08:10.213
♪

08:12.167 --> 08:13.227
Please don't do that.

08:13.252 --> 08:14.060
[SLAP]

08:14.976 --> 08:16.676
♪

08:17.075 --> 08:18.162
That's it?

08:19.016 --> 08:22.774
You're not gonna hit me back?
I just hit you in the face.

08:23.496 --> 08:30.756
♪

08:31.352 --> 08:33.116
Demetrius, what's the Doctor's plan?

08:33.856 --> 08:35.828
Now that he's cured
this Red Rust, what's...

08:36.416 --> 08:38.308
What's this drug have to do with it?

08:39.054 --> 08:41.568
He promised me, Greece would eat.

08:42.054 --> 08:43.515
No one would challenge us.

08:43.615 --> 08:44.995
Because of the drug?

08:45.020 --> 08:47.059
I didn't know anything
about the drug until now.

08:48.275 --> 08:50.186
He said I was the first test case.

08:52.614 --> 08:54.291
Now he knows it works.

08:55.657 --> 08:56.690
Yes.

08:57.734 --> 09:02.234
♪

09:02.654 --> 09:04.763
Demetrius, you were a proud man.

09:05.574 --> 09:07.116
You were a ruler of people.

09:08.272 --> 09:09.354
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

09:09.771 --> 09:11.364
He's taken that from you.

09:11.531 --> 09:13.118
Doesn't that make you angry?

09:14.531 --> 09:16.593
I know I should be angry...

09:19.090 --> 09:21.443
but I-I can't be.

09:21.810 --> 09:26.470
♪

09:26.773 --> 09:28.110
I'd rather be dead.

09:28.210 --> 09:30.790
♪

09:31.497 --> 09:32.571
Sit down.

09:32.977 --> 09:40.906
♪

09:41.105 --> 09:43.835
If something were to happen
to the Doctor's test case,

09:44.262 --> 09:46.617
he'd have to re-evaluate his science.

09:48.417 --> 09:50.046
[CLICK]

09:51.950 --> 09:54.590
And that would buy me some time...

09:55.644 --> 09:57.245
time I sorely need...

09:58.993 --> 10:00.745
to get out of the mess I've created.

10:03.095 --> 10:04.627
Don't worry, Demetrius.

10:06.199 --> 10:07.827
You don't need to get angry.

10:08.295 --> 10:09.195
[GRUNTS]

10:09.233 --> 10:10.259
Open.

10:11.831 --> 10:14.104
Close. Swallow.

10:14.204 --> 10:16.984
[MUFFLED GRUNTING]

10:17.084 --> 10:18.944
[FEET SHUFFLE, CHAIR RATTLES]

10:19.387 --> 10:22.784
[GASPS, GRUNTING]

10:23.996 --> 10:25.630
I'll get angry for you.

10:26.596 --> 10:28.656
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

10:28.756 --> 10:36.496
♪

10:36.596 --> 10:38.056
[DOOR OPENS]

10:38.156 --> 10:39.577
[DOOR CLOSES]

10:45.039 --> 10:46.573
_

10:46.574 --> 10:51.871
♪

10:56.774 --> 10:58.351
[COUGHING]

11:00.079 --> 11:01.179
You okay, Master Chief?

11:01.279 --> 11:02.414
[WHISPERS] I'm fine.

11:04.160 --> 11:05.700
[COUGHING]

11:05.800 --> 11:08.160
[HACKING COUGH]

11:09.600 --> 11:11.537
[PANTING]

11:13.132 --> 11:14.260
[CLEARS THROAT]

11:14.360 --> 11:22.289
♪

11:25.335 --> 11:26.735
I got eyes on target.

11:27.373 --> 11:30.237
Cobra copies. We're in position.

11:31.779 --> 11:33.027
Tiger's on station.

11:33.873 --> 11:36.082
We've got one hell of a welcoming party.

11:36.762 --> 11:39.133
I hold sat dish at the southeast tower.

11:41.641 --> 11:43.593
JETER: We'll find the comms
room at the end of that cable.

11:44.073 --> 11:46.173
Now we just gotta find a quiet way in.

11:46.274 --> 11:48.034
<i>Nathan James,</i> Vulture
Team. We are on station,

11:48.074 --> 11:49.666
preparing to infiltrate target.

11:49.705 --> 11:51.069
Copy that, Vulture Team.

11:51.825 --> 11:53.823
TAO, give us a sitrep.

11:54.225 --> 11:56.492
No sign of surface or air contacts, sir.

11:57.580 --> 12:00.200
All quiet on our end, Vulture.
You are cleared to move in.

12:00.868 --> 12:02.204
Copy that, Mother.

12:03.860 --> 12:05.280
[BIRD CALLS]

12:05.380 --> 12:07.400
- [MEN SHOUTING IN DISTANCE]
- Green.

12:07.500 --> 12:10.280
[SHOUTING CONTINUES]

12:10.817 --> 12:11.997
Those look like fighters.

12:12.097 --> 12:13.917
[MAN SHOUTS INDISTINCTLY]

12:14.017 --> 12:15.157
Those Giorgio's guys?

12:15.257 --> 12:16.917
This must be where he trains them.

12:17.017 --> 12:20.637
Well, there's at least
40 of 'em. Possibly armed.

12:21.164 --> 12:22.984
So much for sneaking in the back door.

12:25.764 --> 12:27.424
[MAN SHOUTS IN GREEK]

12:28.260 --> 12:29.677
So we go in through the front.

12:30.593 --> 12:32.459
His fighters are from all over the region.

12:32.872 --> 12:34.212
Who's gonna notice five more?

12:34.312 --> 12:37.548
Five? There are seven of us.

12:37.832 --> 12:39.268
Looks like it's "boys only."

12:41.733 --> 12:43.797
All teams, rendezvous on my whiskey.

12:44.854 --> 12:48.830
[MEN CONTINUE SHOUTING IN GREEK]

12:52.734 --> 12:56.162
[SHOUTING CONTINUES]

12:58.384 --> 13:00.804
Cooper, the fighters are
approaching your position.

13:01.201 --> 13:02.715
- [STATIC]
- Copy that.

13:03.564 --> 13:05.904
♪

13:06.003 --> 13:08.463
[MAN SHOUTS IN GREEK]

13:08.563 --> 13:11.783
[PANTING]

13:11.883 --> 13:14.494
[MAN SPEAKING IN GREEK]

13:15.306 --> 13:20.166
♪

13:21.129 --> 13:23.244
- Vulture is set.
- Roger.

13:25.729 --> 13:27.629
- Showtime.
- [GUNSHOT]

13:27.654 --> 13:29.958
Ohh!

13:30.489 --> 13:32.601
[SHOUTING IN GREEK] _

13:32.625 --> 13:34.497
_

13:34.521 --> 13:36.061
_

13:38.767 --> 13:40.165
_

13:40.191 --> 13:42.366
Everyone, inside now!

13:42.991 --> 13:44.770
Come on! Inside!

13:45.864 --> 13:46.897
Go!

13:49.105 --> 13:50.685
[MEN SPEAKING IN GREEK]

13:50.785 --> 13:52.765
- [STATIC]
- <i>Nathan James,</i> they're in.

13:52.865 --> 13:53.827
Copy that.

13:55.745 --> 13:59.666
[MEN SPEAKING GREEK]

14:03.505 --> 14:06.925
♪

14:08.049 --> 14:09.145
"Boys only."

14:11.066 --> 14:12.224
Aneurysm?

14:12.378 --> 14:13.738
Well, there's no sign of hemorrhaging.

14:13.818 --> 14:16.298
Perhaps it's something genetic
or chronic or pre-existing.

14:16.378 --> 14:18.642
Pallor's normal. Means death was sudden.

14:20.049 --> 14:21.058
Heart attack?

14:21.097 --> 14:23.757
Could be a heart attack.
Autopsy will tell us that.

14:23.856 --> 14:26.216
GIORGIO: Could it have something
to do with the science, Dad?

14:26.296 --> 14:27.756
No, Giorgio, it could not have had

14:27.856 --> 14:29.636
anything to do with the science.

14:29.736 --> 14:30.896
I could go down to the prison,

14:30.976 --> 14:32.456
pick up more fighters
for you to experiment on.

14:32.536 --> 14:34.116
It is too late for that, Giorgio.

14:34.216 --> 14:36.844
And please do not discuss things
that you do not understand.

14:36.915 --> 14:38.475
Christos and I will get
to the bottom of this.

14:38.548 --> 14:40.388
Of course. Why would
you need either one of us

14:40.468 --> 14:43.283
when you have your golden
child in here to help you?

14:43.788 --> 14:46.368
- You're an asshole, Giorgio.
- Perfect Christos.

14:46.755 --> 14:50.250
Do not speak to your brother
in that tone of voice.

14:50.642 --> 14:51.696
You understand me?

14:51.795 --> 14:54.815
♪

14:55.732 --> 14:57.332
What do you wanna do
in the meantime, Father?

14:57.412 --> 14:59.412
- Meantime? What are you talking about?
- It's no use going

14:59.492 --> 15:00.812
to the drop site if you're not ready,

15:00.892 --> 15:02.912
especially with the Americans after us.

15:03.012 --> 15:04.352
We need to change course,

15:04.452 --> 15:06.212
go somewhere else until you
figure out what happened.

15:06.292 --> 15:08.112
No, no, no, no, no,
no, no. Nothing changes.

15:08.211 --> 15:09.671
Do you hear me? Nothing.

15:09.772 --> 15:11.692
We're not going to stop.
We're not gonna change course.

15:11.772 --> 15:13.672
And we're not going to slow down.

15:14.282 --> 15:15.842
I'm going to find out what killed this man.

15:15.922 --> 15:19.068
And I can tell you right
now it was not my science.

15:20.962 --> 15:22.867
And I'm going to prove that.

15:23.602 --> 15:26.422
[SAW BUZZING]

15:26.719 --> 15:28.055
_

15:29.711 --> 15:31.390
_

15:33.180 --> 15:34.422
[SHOUTING IN GREEK]

15:34.447 --> 15:35.583
[GRUNTS]

15:39.065 --> 15:40.073
MAN: Let's go!

15:40.927 --> 15:42.013
Did you see that?

15:42.353 --> 15:43.585
That guy could've crushed him.

15:44.401 --> 15:45.821
[MEN SHOUTING IN GREEK]

15:45.874 --> 15:47.682
I'm pretty sure we just
snuck into a prison.

15:51.607 --> 15:54.187
- 40 prisoners, 6 guards, 9 guns.
- Come on.

15:54.664 --> 15:55.888
Doesn't add up.

15:56.067 --> 15:57.947
These aren't the fighters
Vellek's going to experiment on.

15:58.027 --> 16:00.306
[MEN SPEAKING GREEK]

16:01.138 --> 16:02.998
These are the ones he's already dosed.

16:03.098 --> 16:04.398
They've got no fight in 'em.

16:04.498 --> 16:06.036
That's about right.
I've seen Vellek's tapes.

16:06.318 --> 16:08.278
So it means we gotta play
nice if we want to blend in.

16:08.358 --> 16:10.018
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS]

16:10.950 --> 16:11.978
What is it?

16:11.979 --> 16:14.077
I've seen that guy from the tapes.

16:14.579 --> 16:16.023
[SPEAKS GREEK]

16:18.819 --> 16:20.839
His name is Ares. He
fought Captain Chandler.

16:20.939 --> 16:21.999
Everyone inside!

16:22.099 --> 16:24.519
Maybe we should have a
little chat with Ares,

16:25.126 --> 16:26.852
get some answers. You read my mind.

16:27.127 --> 16:29.187
Burk, Miller, get Master
Chief to the comms room,

16:29.286 --> 16:31.106
- tap that satellite.
- Yes, sir.

16:31.206 --> 16:32.826
We'll get you on the way out. Good luck.

16:32.926 --> 16:34.946
- DANNY: Good luck.
- MAN: Come on.

16:35.046 --> 16:35.942
Move it.

16:38.584 --> 16:46.206
♪

16:50.779 --> 16:52.079
- One more.
- Good. No, no.

16:52.179 --> 16:53.630
- Come on.
- No more. Thank you.

16:55.030 --> 16:56.116
[CHUCKLES]

16:56.141 --> 16:58.451
To our baby brother. We're gonna miss you.

16:59.141 --> 17:00.041
[INHALES SHARPLY]

17:00.141 --> 17:01.241
- [GLASSES CLINK]
- Cheers.

17:01.341 --> 17:02.961
- Thank you.
- Cheers.

17:03.061 --> 17:04.840
[PIANO PLAYING JAZZ]

17:05.300 --> 17:06.877
So where are you even gonna live?

17:07.398 --> 17:08.618
I don't know yet.

17:08.718 --> 17:10.438
They, uh, set you up with
housing once you get there.

17:10.518 --> 17:11.558
And it's well known the government

17:11.637 --> 17:13.258
always keeps its promises.

17:13.358 --> 17:16.058
- Father, you swore no fighting.
- Not fighting, Lucia, darling.

17:16.157 --> 17:17.538
Just, uh, stating the obvious.

17:17.637 --> 17:19.298
I want Christos to be fully aware

17:19.397 --> 17:21.617
with whom he's climbing into bed.

17:21.718 --> 17:22.858
I know you're upset, Dad,

17:22.958 --> 17:25.137
but not all government scientists are bad.

17:25.238 --> 17:26.578
Not all are bad? I mean,

17:26.678 --> 17:28.979
you're talking about the
people who shunned Dad,

17:29.004 --> 17:32.326
who betrayed him, who drove
him out of his own country.

17:32.764 --> 17:35.264
The proverbial repetition of history...

17:35.364 --> 17:37.904
Mendel, Boltzmann, Copernicus...

17:38.004 --> 17:40.424
all ostracized, all criticized for ideas

17:40.524 --> 17:42.864
that would later on change the world.

17:42.964 --> 17:44.515
And they were all betrayed.

17:44.703 --> 17:47.344
Look, I feel terrible about
leaving when you need me,

17:47.369 --> 17:48.616
but this is something that I...

17:48.641 --> 17:50.523
Hang on, hang on, hang on,
hang on, hang on a second.

17:50.568 --> 17:52.728
Is that what you think this
is about? Me needing you?

17:52.808 --> 17:54.200
- Father.
- The kid grows up...

17:54.225 --> 17:56.403
and disappoints his father.
That's a story as old as time.

17:56.458 --> 17:58.769
But don't think for one
second that I <i>need</i> you.

17:59.129 --> 18:02.669
♪

18:02.882 --> 18:03.909
Christos...

18:04.009 --> 18:05.469
♪

18:05.983 --> 18:08.629
[CHRISTOS SIGHS DEEPLY]

18:08.729 --> 18:11.549
♪

18:12.702 --> 18:13.600
Love you.

18:14.062 --> 18:20.726
♪

18:23.778 --> 18:26.159
Take a look right under
there. Look at that tissue.

18:26.184 --> 18:28.004
I have. There's nothing going on.

18:28.104 --> 18:30.972
But I will find out what
killed this dude, I promise you.

18:31.024 --> 18:31.983
You will?

18:31.984 --> 18:34.004
♪

18:34.656 --> 18:36.436
- Giorgio.
- What?

18:36.536 --> 18:38.679
- Is everything okay?
- I don't know, man.

18:38.704 --> 18:41.190
But we're still on schedule,
right? For my seeds?

18:41.664 --> 18:45.357
Yes. England will get
their delivery as promised.

18:46.037 --> 18:47.496
Good, because if there's a problem,

18:47.757 --> 18:50.417
if your father's doing something
dangerous, we can deal with it.

18:51.011 --> 18:52.569
We're in this together, you and I.

18:54.957 --> 18:57.117
- Are we?
- Of course.

18:59.225 --> 19:00.658
No, I can't help you.

19:01.439 --> 19:03.651
My old man... he's gonna
do what he's gonna do.

19:04.397 --> 19:10.617
♪

19:11.673 --> 19:13.258
[GUN CLACKING]

19:13.283 --> 19:14.803
Danny and Wolf have gone off script.

19:14.883 --> 19:17.212
They're still in the courtyard.
The rest of them made it inside.

19:17.573 --> 19:20.872
And it looks as though
Green has found a new friend.

19:21.213 --> 19:23.233
♪

19:23.333 --> 19:24.318
Ares.

19:24.533 --> 19:26.553
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS]

19:27.135 --> 19:28.156
Who are you?

19:28.335 --> 19:29.773
A friend of Tom Chandler.

19:31.495 --> 19:33.115
I think you know him as Hercules.

19:33.832 --> 19:34.777
Hercules.

19:34.815 --> 19:36.675
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS CONTINUE]

19:37.780 --> 19:40.206
Is he... like me now?

19:41.808 --> 19:44.235
No. He got out in time.

19:45.117 --> 19:46.068
Good.

19:47.557 --> 19:48.457
That's good.

19:48.557 --> 19:50.017
Hey, what's going on in here?

19:50.041 --> 19:51.315
_

19:51.316 --> 19:53.008
[SPEAKING GREEK]

19:54.250 --> 19:55.517
_

19:57.297 --> 19:58.649
_

19:59.814 --> 20:01.363
What, you don't speak Greek?

20:02.338 --> 20:03.589
I said move!

20:04.740 --> 20:06.874
♪

20:07.469 --> 20:08.412
I'm going.

20:10.694 --> 20:13.474
Got to get inside, tough guy.

20:14.294 --> 20:15.914
Got to eat your lunch

20:16.014 --> 20:19.404
so you can stay big and strong!

20:20.534 --> 20:27.517
♪

20:30.543 --> 20:34.914
♪

20:35.912 --> 20:37.490
[SPEAKING GREEK] _

20:37.514 --> 20:38.853
_

20:39.690 --> 20:40.976
You're not supposed to be here.

20:41.850 --> 20:44.630
I'm... going to the cafeteria.

20:45.063 --> 20:48.069
Then you're not even on the
right floor, idiot. Come on.

20:48.849 --> 20:55.390
♪

20:55.490 --> 20:58.990
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS]

20:59.090 --> 21:05.500
♪

21:08.650 --> 21:15.032
♪

21:18.290 --> 21:22.750
♪

21:24.319 --> 21:26.319
[SWITCH CLICKS, WHIRRING]

21:28.155 --> 21:29.895
<i>Nathan James,</i>
Vulture, this is Cobra.

21:29.994 --> 21:31.549
<i>We've made it into the control room.</i>

21:31.904 --> 21:34.294
Copy that, Cobra. We
hear you loud and clear.

21:34.394 --> 21:37.440
- Standing by for uplink.
- <i>BURK: Roger. Will advise.</i>

21:38.236 --> 21:40.609
How long will it take to tap
into the satellite signal?

21:40.649 --> 21:42.125
Depends on the level of encryption.

21:42.183 --> 21:44.003
I'd say around 20 minutes. Once we uplink,

21:44.103 --> 21:46.223
the ship can start processing
the communications log.

21:46.303 --> 21:49.223
- But first, we gotta find that satellite.
- [COMPUTER CHIRPING]

21:50.743 --> 21:51.974
Why are you following me?

21:52.297 --> 21:53.924
Because I have questions, Ares.

21:54.257 --> 21:56.436
The drugs they're giving
you, how long do they last?

21:57.199 --> 21:58.269
I don't know.

21:59.017 --> 22:01.767
I can't fight. I want to, but...

22:02.846 --> 22:03.759
I can't.

22:03.884 --> 22:07.277
♪

22:07.377 --> 22:09.596
On your feet, animal.

22:10.137 --> 22:13.237
♪

22:13.337 --> 22:14.717
[MEN SPEAKING GREEK]

22:15.357 --> 22:17.381
I don't know how I missed you,

22:18.055 --> 22:20.102
the biggest guy in the room.

22:21.197 --> 22:24.396
I bet everyone was afraid of you, huh?

22:26.618 --> 22:28.829
Look at tough guy now.

22:30.498 --> 22:33.080
Just big... dumb...

22:34.480 --> 22:35.480
animal.

22:36.399 --> 22:37.762
Am I wrong?

22:40.479 --> 22:42.779
- [ELECTRICITY ZAPS]
- Aah! [GRUNTS]

22:42.879 --> 22:44.619
[GROANS]

22:44.719 --> 22:47.699
[INHALING SHARPLY]

22:48.454 --> 22:49.969
- Does it hurt?
- [GRUNTS]

22:50.057 --> 22:51.319
Do you want to hit me?

22:51.530 --> 22:53.670
Get up. Up. Come on!

22:53.770 --> 22:56.670
[BREATHING DEEPLY]

22:57.151 --> 22:59.211
- Again.
- [CONTINUES BREATHING DEEPLY]

22:59.758 --> 23:02.352
I want to see how angry you can get.

23:02.798 --> 23:04.358
Where should I hit you next?

23:04.678 --> 23:05.627
Here...

23:07.278 --> 23:08.490
or here?

23:10.998 --> 23:12.174
Here.

23:14.292 --> 23:15.761
[SPEAKING GREEK] _

23:15.786 --> 23:17.786
_

23:18.333 --> 23:20.565
_

23:20.707 --> 23:22.115
_

23:26.517 --> 23:27.568
[SPEAKS GREEK] _

23:27.598 --> 23:32.038
♪

23:36.788 --> 23:42.768
♪

23:44.386 --> 23:46.006
A man shouldn't drink alone.

23:46.106 --> 23:47.414
You get used to it.

23:49.908 --> 23:52.066
You know you're gonna be
a hero in England, right?

23:52.396 --> 23:54.885
Oh, goodie. Just what I've always wanted.

23:56.034 --> 23:57.422
I can guarantee you,

23:58.049 --> 23:59.616
I won't be the one taking the bows.

23:59.715 --> 24:02.385
That's for the old man. <i>Il maestro.</i>

24:03.096 --> 24:04.596
Doesn't seem fair, does it?

24:04.696 --> 24:07.756
You do all the dirty work, and
your dad gets all the glory.

24:08.302 --> 24:11.971
My dad likes to say, "Not
only is life not fair,

24:12.169 --> 24:14.014
"no one ever promised it would be.

24:14.422 --> 24:15.731
You make your own fate."

24:16.022 --> 24:19.002
Well, I hope he appreciates
what you've done.

24:19.102 --> 24:20.122
[GLASSES CLINK]

24:20.222 --> 24:22.114
He's not thinking that clearly right now.

24:22.540 --> 24:25.280
Of course. He's got a lot on his plate.

24:26.069 --> 24:28.733
Curing the Red Rust,
abolishing world hunger...

24:29.220 --> 24:30.502
mind control.

24:32.944 --> 24:35.272
Who said anything about mind control?

24:36.194 --> 24:37.099
You did.

24:38.198 --> 24:39.048
Did I?

24:41.498 --> 24:42.452
No.

24:43.549 --> 24:46.444
The mind stays the same. It's
the behavior that changes.

24:47.022 --> 24:49.293
That's what makes the
torture that much greater.

24:50.262 --> 24:51.384
Imagine...

24:52.742 --> 24:55.322
knowing what you want...

24:55.865 --> 24:58.686
[HUFFS] and not being able to fight for it.

25:00.265 --> 25:01.341
Well...

25:06.327 --> 25:07.457
Giorgio, listen to me.

25:08.796 --> 25:11.744
Your father's already proven he
can cure the world of Red Rust.

25:12.356 --> 25:13.451
He can feed everyone.

25:14.196 --> 25:15.976
Talk about a more perfect world.

25:16.076 --> 25:17.336
That's a legacy.

25:17.911 --> 25:20.216
But if he's got other
designs, dangerous designs,

25:20.241 --> 25:23.644
then he goes from a hero
to a monster like that.

25:25.570 --> 25:27.939
If you really want to protect
him <i>and</i> his legacy,

25:29.122 --> 25:30.610
protect him from himself.

25:36.683 --> 25:38.346
Good talk, 007.

25:39.003 --> 25:45.637
♪

25:46.606 --> 25:48.466
♪

25:49.010 --> 25:50.055
Found it.

25:51.370 --> 25:53.390
[SHOUTS IN GREEK, GRUNTS] _

25:53.490 --> 25:57.474
[GRUNTING]

26:02.610 --> 26:03.790
[BONES CRUNCH]

26:03.890 --> 26:08.110
♪

26:08.914 --> 26:11.094
I don't think you need to do that.

26:11.194 --> 26:16.774
♪

26:17.081 --> 26:18.560
You know I could hurt you.

26:19.770 --> 26:20.901
Yes.

26:21.464 --> 26:22.444
Right.

26:22.962 --> 26:24.662
So you're gonna get the hell outta here

26:24.762 --> 26:25.706
and you're gonna keep your mouth shut,

26:25.986 --> 26:28.449
or I promise, I will hurt you.

26:34.185 --> 26:38.925
♪

26:39.025 --> 26:40.085
[CHIRPING]

26:40.185 --> 26:41.965
♪

26:42.948 --> 26:44.708
<i>Nathan James,</i> we've
cracked the satellite signal.

26:44.788 --> 26:47.005
<i>Sending you its ID and
coordinates for uplink.</i>

26:48.173 --> 26:50.288
We're on it, Cobra.
Stand by for confirmation.

26:50.917 --> 26:52.857
I see no sign of hemorrhage.

26:52.894 --> 26:55.143
I see no sign of genetic deficiency.

26:55.206 --> 26:58.244
We've done the blood tests.
Have to start on the heart.

26:58.526 --> 26:59.568
[DOOR CLOSES]

27:05.202 --> 27:07.262
What do you want, Giorgio? We're working.

27:07.291 --> 27:08.295
[CLEARS THROAT]

27:10.237 --> 27:11.502
What do you want?

27:12.246 --> 27:13.422
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

27:13.752 --> 27:14.863
I was thinking...

27:15.362 --> 27:16.622
you cured the Red Rust.

27:17.435 --> 27:19.175
Why don't we go home for a little while,

27:19.275 --> 27:20.375
until things cool off?

27:20.475 --> 27:21.956
Then you can ship out the product.

27:22.395 --> 27:23.655
The world can wait.

27:23.755 --> 27:25.475
Are you suggesting that
we just give up, Giorgio?

27:25.555 --> 27:26.695
Is that what you're doing?

27:26.795 --> 27:28.395
Because if you're suggesting
that we just give up,

27:28.475 --> 27:30.795
why don't you have the balls
to say exactly what you mean?

27:30.971 --> 27:32.511
Dad, it's not giving up.

27:33.219 --> 27:35.902
- It is a safe move.
- [SCALPEL THUDS]

27:36.253 --> 27:38.894
You know, Giorgio, you leave me speechless.

27:38.963 --> 27:42.213
- And now compound your innate ignorance...
- [INHALES SHARPLY]

27:42.340 --> 27:43.640
with weakness.

27:44.210 --> 27:46.256
I have no words for what you are.

27:46.705 --> 27:47.685
Get out.

27:48.333 --> 27:50.118
Let's go back to work, Christos.

27:50.866 --> 27:52.286
[INHALES SHARPLY]

27:52.386 --> 27:58.046
♪

27:59.018 --> 28:00.541
How often are you injected?

28:01.445 --> 28:02.585
Only once.

28:02.685 --> 28:04.225
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS]

28:04.325 --> 28:06.305
[TRAYS CLATTER]

28:06.405 --> 28:10.388
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS CONTINUE]

28:16.205 --> 28:18.585
Ares, if they only injected you once,

28:18.685 --> 28:20.465
how are they keeping all of you like this?

28:20.565 --> 28:28.305
♪

28:29.093 --> 28:30.887
Ares, is the drug in the food?

28:32.213 --> 28:34.993
No. The drug <i>is</i> the food.

28:35.093 --> 28:40.513
♪

28:40.613 --> 28:43.313
[MAN SPEAKS GREEK]

28:43.413 --> 28:46.473
[TRAYS CLATTER]

28:46.573 --> 28:49.584
[UTENSILS CLINKING]

28:52.893 --> 28:58.733
♪

29:05.173 --> 29:10.273
♪

29:13.956 --> 29:16.096
You again. It's not that big a ship.

29:16.196 --> 29:18.102
It's not that small either.

29:20.638 --> 29:23.604
I can't fight my father. He's too strong.

29:23.979 --> 29:26.039
No, Giorgio, you're not fighting him.

29:26.659 --> 29:27.892
You're protecting him.

29:29.979 --> 29:33.699
[MEN SPEAKING GREEK]

29:38.389 --> 29:39.624
What would I have to do?

29:40.029 --> 29:41.416
Just let me call England.

29:41.909 --> 29:43.829
They'll send scientists
to safeguard the cure.

29:43.909 --> 29:46.198
We'll take your father in,
get him the help that he needs,

29:46.306 --> 29:47.485
that he deserves.

29:48.191 --> 29:50.352
He'll still be known as
the man that fed the world.

29:50.950 --> 29:55.410
♪

29:55.830 --> 29:59.130
It's too late. We're almost to Malta.

29:59.733 --> 30:01.433
- Malta? What...
- You can't stop him.

30:01.533 --> 30:03.633
What's Malta? Is that... is
that the drop site, Giorgio?

30:03.733 --> 30:06.433
- What's the plan?
- Look, man, don't worry about it, okay?

30:06.533 --> 30:07.666
A deal's a deal.

30:08.229 --> 30:10.929
My old man will get your
people the cure, as promised.

30:11.029 --> 30:12.129
The rest is...

30:12.229 --> 30:14.449
What? Giorgio, what's the rest?

30:14.549 --> 30:16.929
World domination? Turning
your enemies into sheep?

30:17.029 --> 30:20.609
You don't understand him. No one does.

30:21.049 --> 30:22.502
That's 'cause he's insane.

30:24.368 --> 30:25.529
Let me help you.

30:26.478 --> 30:28.168
It doesn't have to play out like this.

30:31.857 --> 30:34.931
I'm starting to dislike you, Commander.

30:35.558 --> 30:38.438
♪

30:41.838 --> 30:43.338
[COMPUTER CHIRPS]

30:43.438 --> 30:45.738
♪

30:46.494 --> 30:48.063
Sir, we have decryption.

30:51.237 --> 30:53.603
- The ship's coordinates.
- Yes, sir.

30:54.643 --> 30:57.033
And the older ones match
those from Giorgio's mansion.

30:57.323 --> 30:58.639
Gotcha, asshole.

30:59.459 --> 31:01.287
Cobra, we have confirmation.

31:01.319 --> 31:03.353
- Copy that.
- [SWITCH CLICKS]

31:04.441 --> 31:06.175
All right. Nice work, Master Chief.

31:06.199 --> 31:07.440
Let's get the hell out of here.

31:08.239 --> 31:09.979
[MAN SPEAKING GREEK]

31:10.079 --> 31:11.240
Hey, tough guy.

31:12.399 --> 31:13.574
What's wrong?

31:14.885 --> 31:17.739
You don't like bread? You don't like rice?

31:17.839 --> 31:19.899
Everyone likes rice.

31:20.573 --> 31:22.516
Eat. Now.

31:28.093 --> 31:29.244
Stand up.

31:30.778 --> 31:31.838
Stand up!

31:33.739 --> 31:37.624
[MEN SPEAKING GREEK]

31:39.580 --> 31:40.596
Hey!

31:41.392 --> 31:43.165
[SPEAKS GREEK] _

31:44.499 --> 31:47.739
[GRUNTING]

31:49.979 --> 31:52.228
- [CRUNCH]
- [GRUNTS]

31:56.922 --> 31:58.622
[LABORED BREATHING]

31:58.714 --> 32:01.294
- We gotta go. Can you walk?
- [COUGHING]

32:01.773 --> 32:03.264
I said, eat!

32:04.515 --> 32:07.135
[ALARM BLARING]

32:07.888 --> 32:09.308
That doesn't sound good.

32:09.408 --> 32:12.887
[ALARM CONTINUES BLARING]

32:13.568 --> 32:16.428
♪

32:16.528 --> 32:20.480
[GRUNTING]

32:23.512 --> 32:25.340
Who's the tough guy now, <i>vlaka?</i>

32:25.672 --> 32:27.043
Ares, come on.

32:27.147 --> 32:28.967
- [ELECTRICITY ZAPS]
- Aah!

32:29.231 --> 32:30.291
[GRUNTS]

32:33.348 --> 32:37.067
[GRUNTING]

32:43.042 --> 32:44.382
[TRAY CLANGS AND CLATTERS]

32:44.482 --> 32:47.062
- [MAN SHOUTS IN GREEK]
- Hey! Come on!

32:47.162 --> 32:48.582
You can be free!

32:49.844 --> 32:52.143
[MAN SHOUTS IN GREEK]

32:53.000 --> 32:54.700
Tell Hercules to keep fighting.

32:55.480 --> 32:57.140
[GUNSHOTS]

32:58.006 --> 32:59.121
[THUD]

32:59.406 --> 33:01.106
- [STATIC]
- <i>Nathan James,</i> we're blown.

33:01.131 --> 33:02.531
Request immediate extract.

33:02.717 --> 33:05.377
Copy that, Vulture.
Sunshine's heading your way.

33:05.476 --> 33:07.216
♪

33:07.316 --> 33:09.216
[MEN SHOUTING IN GREEK]

33:09.316 --> 33:10.900
[GUNSHOTS]

33:11.618 --> 33:13.976
- DANNY: Is he hit?
- No, but he's hurt.

33:14.076 --> 33:16.576
[ALARM CONTINUES BLARING]

33:16.676 --> 33:19.616
♪

33:20.079 --> 33:21.449
[GUNSHOTS]

33:23.316 --> 33:25.936
[MEN SHOUT IN GREEK]

33:26.491 --> 33:28.376
[GUNFIRE]

33:28.843 --> 33:31.363
- Uhh!
- [GUNFIRE CONTINUES]

33:35.969 --> 33:37.576
[MEN SHOUTING IN GREEK]

33:37.676 --> 33:43.559
♪

33:45.796 --> 33:47.856
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS IN DISTANCE]

33:49.432 --> 33:50.672
Mate, I need to use that radio.

33:50.752 --> 33:53.152
I already told you, you're not allowed.

33:55.913 --> 33:59.141
[GRUNTING]

34:00.913 --> 34:03.493
- [GRUNTS]
- [BONES CRUNCH, BODY THUDS]

34:03.593 --> 34:05.593
♪

34:11.117 --> 34:13.257
♪

34:14.444 --> 34:17.264
So Vellek isn't just injecting
the fighters with Nostos,

34:17.364 --> 34:19.464
he's baking it right into their food.

34:19.563 --> 34:20.897
It appears so, sir.

34:21.146 --> 34:22.795
So that's why he wanted the seeds.

34:22.828 --> 34:24.608
He cures the Red Rust, mixes in the Nostos

34:24.706 --> 34:26.855
to create food that'll pacify his enemies.

34:27.076 --> 34:29.288
It's the perfect weapon. People
eating it won't even know.

34:29.387 --> 34:31.347
Well, even if they did,
what choice would they have?

34:31.427 --> 34:34.087
- They either eat it or starve.
- Jesus.

34:35.118 --> 34:37.933
Your work paid off. We
narrowed down our search area.

34:38.099 --> 34:39.799
But now Vellek knows we're coming.

34:39.828 --> 34:41.091
He always knew.

34:41.619 --> 34:44.043
Sir, we're getting an
incoming transmission.

34:44.168 --> 34:46.188
- Broadcast the call.
- Aye, sir.

34:46.289 --> 34:48.809
<i>I say again,</i> Nathan James, <i>this</i>
<i>is Commander James Fletcher.</i>

34:49.444 --> 34:51.695
<i>- You were right...</i>
- Can we triangulate that signal?

34:51.719 --> 34:54.130
No, sir. It's coming from
satellite... untraceable.

34:54.353 --> 34:55.774
A biological weapon,

34:55.811 --> 34:58.038
something to do with behavior control.

34:59.434 --> 35:01.354
I'm not sure exactly how
he's planning on using it,

35:01.434 --> 35:02.994
but we're in a warship headed to Malta.

35:03.074 --> 35:06.134
<i>I say again, we're headed
to Malta. You must stop him.</i>

35:06.533 --> 35:07.953
<i>You're the only ones who can.</i>

35:08.053 --> 35:09.993
<i>I know this doesn't
make things right.</i>

35:10.093 --> 35:12.773
<i>You must believe me, I only
did this to serve my country.</i>

35:14.891 --> 35:16.752
Sasha, I'm so sorry I hurt you.

35:17.171 --> 35:19.111
<i>I hope even if you don't forgive me,</i>

35:19.211 --> 35:21.291
<i>that you'll understand.
I never meant to hurt...</i>

35:21.371 --> 35:23.031
[STATIC HISSING]

35:23.131 --> 35:24.311
What happened?

35:25.249 --> 35:26.232
[CLICK]

35:27.170 --> 35:28.186
Come on.

35:30.622 --> 35:32.067
We lost the signal.

35:32.343 --> 35:39.043
♪

35:39.072 --> 35:40.056
Malta.

35:40.783 --> 35:42.210
That sounds about right.

35:43.463 --> 35:45.723
♪

35:47.023 --> 35:48.243
[DOOR OPENS]

35:48.268 --> 35:49.928
- Giorgio...
- Who were you talking to?

35:49.953 --> 35:51.601
- I know you have your doubts...
- [DOOR CLOSES]

35:52.148 --> 35:53.466
but we have to do something.

35:53.816 --> 35:55.988
We have to stop your father. He's gone mad.

35:57.426 --> 35:59.024
We can make things right.

36:03.720 --> 36:05.464
Does anyone else know you're here?

36:08.414 --> 36:09.896
Did you get through to anyone?

36:11.096 --> 36:13.263
No. I couldn't get a signal.

36:13.745 --> 36:15.936
Okay. Okay.

36:17.529 --> 36:18.715
Just hang on.

36:18.969 --> 36:23.109
♪

36:23.798 --> 36:24.910
[DOOR OPENS]

36:25.009 --> 36:31.069
♪

36:32.045 --> 36:33.264
[SIGHS]

36:33.265 --> 36:35.685
You really think you could
turn my own son against me, man?

36:36.125 --> 36:39.263
Huh? You don't get it. We're family.

36:39.863 --> 36:42.283
Whatever the crap between
us, his blood is my blood.

36:42.383 --> 36:45.283
And you're a punk, Fletcher. A con man.

36:45.383 --> 36:47.043
Matter of fact, a two-bit con man.

36:47.561 --> 36:49.061
I found this buried deep

36:49.161 --> 36:51.461
in the tissue in the
esophagus of Demetrius.

36:51.561 --> 36:53.401
Your little poison pill.

36:55.540 --> 36:57.040
I mean, who in the hell do you think

36:57.140 --> 36:58.603
you're dealing with here, Fletcher?!

36:59.311 --> 37:01.531
My science was perfect!
My mind's like a knife!

37:01.631 --> 37:03.384
You can't play me.

37:04.711 --> 37:07.651
[SIGHS DEEPLY] I'm just
so disappointed in you.

37:08.292 --> 37:10.392
I invited you on my ship. I feed you.

37:10.492 --> 37:12.232
I was gonna feed your entire country.

37:12.332 --> 37:13.758
[LAUGHING]

37:15.412 --> 37:17.032
[CONTINUES LAUGHING]

37:17.563 --> 37:18.889
You're a lunatic.

37:18.890 --> 37:20.190
No, no, no, Fletcher.

37:20.601 --> 37:23.181
A lunatic is the mind
that refuses to evolve.

37:23.281 --> 37:25.621
Lunacy is this world, here and now,

37:25.721 --> 37:27.861
doing the same thing over and over,

37:27.961 --> 37:31.141
going down the same street,
falling in the same manhole,

37:31.241 --> 37:33.543
and expecting different results.

37:34.162 --> 37:36.293
The sad cycle of failure.

37:36.879 --> 37:38.560
But I'm gonna change all that.

37:39.039 --> 37:41.379
I'll ask you one more
time. Who did you call?

37:41.479 --> 37:43.068
It doesn't matter, son.

37:43.879 --> 37:45.619
They're not gonna stop us now.

37:45.719 --> 37:48.659
So now what? Are you gonna kill me?

37:49.509 --> 37:52.997
No, man. I don't kill
you. I abhor violence.

37:56.589 --> 37:58.435
[SIGHS] Giorgio, listen.

37:58.740 --> 38:01.000
I understand why you told
him. I do. But we can fix this.

38:01.100 --> 38:03.080
You and me together, we
can make things right...

38:03.180 --> 38:04.266
[GUNSHOT]

38:04.291 --> 38:08.588
♪

38:11.020 --> 38:14.360
♪

38:14.460 --> 38:16.480
[WAVES CRASHING]

38:16.580 --> 38:24.482
♪

38:29.765 --> 38:32.699
The guy who caused all our
problems may have just solved them.

38:33.525 --> 38:35.213
Or maybe this is another trick.

38:35.725 --> 38:37.363
Either way, we'll handle it.

38:38.491 --> 38:40.968
But my guess is you were
always right about him.

38:43.481 --> 38:46.261
Well, if that's the truth,
it probably cost him his life.

38:48.445 --> 38:55.992
♪

38:58.045 --> 39:05.552
♪

39:07.621 --> 39:13.992
♪

39:17.205 --> 39:20.945
♪

39:22.671 --> 39:23.860
[POT THUDS]

39:23.885 --> 39:27.892
♪

39:28.596 --> 39:31.200
[MUFFLED SHOUTING]

39:32.080 --> 39:33.620
[GRUNTS]

39:33.720 --> 39:40.627
♪

39:44.937 --> 39:48.488
♪

39:54.770 --> 39:56.356
- [EXHALES]
- [GLASSES CLATTER]

39:56.423 --> 39:57.595
[SIGHS]

39:59.007 --> 40:06.509
♪

40:08.367 --> 40:09.427
♪

40:09.527 --> 40:11.115
[SIGHS HEAVILY]

40:12.897 --> 40:13.992
Hey, Dad.

40:15.628 --> 40:17.368
Christos, I was worried about you.

40:17.468 --> 40:18.687
What are you worried about?

40:18.948 --> 40:21.678
The Nostos blended seamlessly
with the Red Rust cure.

40:21.890 --> 40:23.288
No need for injections.

40:23.543 --> 40:25.363
- One plant now contains it all.
- Huh.

40:25.854 --> 40:28.283
- You really did it.
- I did it, didn't I?

40:28.736 --> 40:30.116
It's gonna be a bumper crop.

40:31.048 --> 40:33.748
The secret was in just one base pair

40:33.848 --> 40:37.045
on the fourth DNA strand
of <i>Elaeis virilis,</i>

40:37.070 --> 40:38.978
our beautiful palm seed.

40:39.944 --> 40:41.504
Come and look at it. It's magnificent.

40:42.032 --> 40:43.963
- Come on, come on.
- [CHUCKLES]

40:44.352 --> 40:46.231
- [SIGHS]
- Okay, it's just one...

40:46.672 --> 40:49.612
- one switch, A to G.
- [WHISPERS] Whoa.

40:49.712 --> 40:51.012
No, look, look, look, look.

40:51.112 --> 40:54.452
It's one switch, A to
G, on that one base pair.

40:54.552 --> 40:57.512
That's it. That's it. Nothing
more complicated than that.

40:57.899 --> 41:00.439
But I-I-I-I'm making it so complicated.

41:00.539 --> 41:02.099
I mean, I can't believe I'm
making it so complicated.

41:02.179 --> 41:04.599
It's like a schoolboy
could have figured this out.

41:04.699 --> 41:06.946
And yet it got by me. It got by you.

41:07.172 --> 41:09.982
It's magnificent. <i>Semplice.</i>

41:10.492 --> 41:13.292
[SPEAKS ITALIAN]

41:16.465 --> 41:19.196
You are the most magnificent son.

41:19.652 --> 41:22.072
Love you. Love you, love you, love you,

41:22.172 --> 41:25.244
love you more than olives,
and I really love olives.

41:26.675 --> 41:27.851
Let me look.

41:29.077 --> 41:30.014
God.

41:30.993 --> 41:32.362
It's magnificent, huh?

41:32.572 --> 41:36.772
♪

